3546	  \emph{(iii) A retract of a finite-colimit-preserving functor preserves finite colimits.} If \(G\)
3547	  sends a finite colimit cocone to a colimit cocone and \(F\) is a retract of \(G\), then the colimit
3548	  comparison map for \(F\) is a retract of the (isomorphism) comparison map for \(G\), hence itself an
3549	  isomorphism, so \(F\) preserves that colimit. Applying this with \(F = \mathrm{toSheaf}\,R\) and
3550	  \(G = L \circ \mathrm{toSheaf}\,R\), we conclude that \(\mathrm{toSheaf}\,R\) preserves finite
3551	  colimits.
