3555	[The underlying-abelian-sheaf functor preserves epimorphisms]
3556	  \label{lem:to_sheaf_preserves_epi}
3557	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.toSheaf_preservesEpimorphisms}
3558	  \uses{lem:toSheaf_preservesFiniteColimits, lem:preservesEpi_of_preservesColimitsOfShape_mathlib}
3559	  \textit{Project-bespoke gap-fill (instance).}
3560	  The forgetful functor from sheaves of \(\mathcal{O}_X\)-modules to the underlying sheaves of
3561	  abelian groups preserves epimorphisms: if \(g : S_2 \to S_3\) is an epimorphism of
3562	  \(\mathcal{O}_X\)-modules then the induced morphism of underlying abelian sheaves is an
3563	  epimorphism. This is the one small instance unlocking the passage from a module epimorphism to
3564	  local surjectivity in Lemma~\ref{lem:affine_surj_of_vanishing}.
3565	\end{lemma}
